    "synopsis": "Sergeant Ashel of the Raven Guard stalks a world in revolt, his orders to silence a rising stirred up by the Alpha Legion. His ally on the operation is unlikely: a Night Lord who has refused his own legion's treachery, and who still treats terror as the keenest weapon in his armoury. As the loyalist pair tighten the noose around their quarry, Ashel finds himself measuring his own methods against a brother whose lessons feel at once kin to the XIX Legion's shadow craft and abomination to it, and asks what the real difference is when both legions wage their wars in the language of fear.",
